An 11-year-old boy, identified as Ibrahim Ali, on Friday got drowned while swimming in a pond. The spokesman for the State Fire Service, Saminu Abdullahi, who confirmed the incident to Saturday PUNCH on Friday, said, “At about 10:33 am, the service received a call from one Ibrahim Burga.” Following the distress call, he said firefighters mobilised and arrived at the scene at Gundawa junction at 10:45 am, pulled the remains of the victim out of the pond. According to him, the remains of the victim were handed over to the ward head of his immediate community, Sa’adu Ahmad, who in turn handed over the victim to his parent. As of the time of filing this report, it was learnt that the victim had since been buried according to Muslim injunctions.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com